^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|I wanted to discuss the bidding, but hope made two declarer miscue which require to discuss. First, the spade play. The correct play is to let the 10 ride. All things being equal, it is a pure guess as to whether or not West had the King and not the Jack. But, the one case where it is right for sure is if West has both the King and Jack, as on this hand. So, because of that 25% chance, it is right to let the spade ride. You will come out ahead 25% of the time, the rest of the time it is a guess anyway.|
PG| ***** 40 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The other play was the diamond at trick seven. You were in danger of running out of trumps at that point, as you did. So, you should set up your clubs ASAP. Play 2 rounds of clubs and the suit will be set up, and you still have two trump left. In that fashion you will make the hand. There was no reason to play a diamond. In general, there is no reason for declarer to voluntarily shorten herself. You should shorten dummy to set up ruffs which are extra tricks. But declarer does not get extra tricks by ruffing. A long trump is a long trump, whether you ruff or just play it out. There are many reasons to set up declarer's side suits before running out of trump.|
PG| ***** 41 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now as to the bidding. I like to play 1N is still forcing by a passed hand  but some do not. The problem with playing it not forcing is a hand such as mine, a limit raise with three card support. If you decide not to play 1N forcing by a passed hand, then you should play Drury. Otherwise a hand such as mine is not biddable. |
PG| ***** 42 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The final point is whether or not Eddy should open. I think it is fine to pass. A 4-3-3-3 hand with 12 counts are not particularly good hands. On the other hand, Eddy does have good HCP and some extra 10s. By Bergen adjust 3, he could add an extra Starting Point. In adjust-3 you add one point for when Aces/tens exceed the Queens/Jacks. So, I think I might open, but as I said pass is quite reasonable.|
