^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Several kibs asked me about Inverted Minors in competition. I recommend against inverted minors in competition. In competition Jordan 2N or redouble is available to show the strong diamond raise. Therefore, both 2D and 3D are weak raises. 3D just shows better diamonds. Pam, with her singleton heart and 5 great diamonds has a clear 3D bid over 1D. It is likely the opponents have a major suit fit, probably in hearts. Indeed, the opps can make 3H.|
