^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Nicely played Pam. You were down due to Terry's over enthusiasm. ^*BIn general, you should have at least an opening hand to overcall over a preempt^*N. There are a few exceptions, but Terry's hand is not one of them. He has nice clubs but only five and he has spades, which means he does not fit well with pard. So, he should pass. If he had something like x KQJxxx Axxx xx, he could consider 3H because there are many hands where 4H makes. But with a long minor that is not solid, there is not much upside to making a light overcall.|
